      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided that linear elastic constitutive model is appropriate for the loading regime (sub-yield stiffness and yield force QoIs); nonlinear geometry effects evaluated.",
      "rationale": "For construct stiffness and yield force QoIs, linear elastic model with von Mises yield criterion is appropriate. Large-displacement effects (NLGEOM) enabled; pre-yield force-displacement response is quasi-linear. Bilinear isotropic hardening used post-yield for force-at-40mm QoI. Model form choice documented and peer reviewed. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric inputs from calibrated CMM measurements of as-built hardware; all inputs traceable to primary measurement records.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (E = 114.2 GPa), yield strength (σ_y = 896 MPa), and tangent modulus sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon dataset (dataset ID: nagaraja-material-props-Ti6Al4V-2025; dataVintage 2025-10-10). The material dataset was acquired three weeks before the model's November mesh-refinement revision (modelRevisionDate 2025-11-03). The mesh update altered only element size and contact formulation; the constitutive law and its parameterization were unchanged, so the pre-revision material dataset was retained without re-characterization. Geometric inputs from CMM survey of N=3 screw specimens (mean ± SD reported). All inputs traceable to calibrated instruments. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
