      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios or sensitivity analysis demonstrates QoI insensitivity to untested conditions.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 load configuration (compression-bending, 10° offset). Alternative load angles and axial preload conditions not explored. Sensitivity analysis was not performed for off-axis loading. Required Gradation 2 not achieved; factor remains at Gradation 1. This is a documented shortfall acknowledged in the credibility assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs (material properties, geometry, boundary conditions) demonstrably match experimental specimen and test fixture conditions.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry (UHMWPE block dimensions, screw insertion depth, inter-block distance 100 mm). Material inputs matched to same production lot. Fixture compliance measured and incorporated as spring elements. Equivalency confirmed by parameter-by-parameter comparison table. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
