      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical risk of construct failure and are the quantities predicted by the model in the COU.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force and force at 40 mm are standard ASTM F1717 performance metrics directly tied to fatigue life and fracture risk. QoIs identical between validation activity and COU. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
